@spec gm_propagate_spec  src=tests/specs/gm_propagate_spec.lua  loc=223  sha=f8aa484  cases=8
@exercises groupManager (gm), trackerManager (h.tm)
@surface   gm:markGroup, gm:newInstance, tm:flush, gm:assignEvent, gm:addEvent, gm:setLocalMode

# Intent
  Stateful mirror manager (gm). Wraps the pure mirror core with anchor
  maths and rides tm's preflush/postflush seam: a staged edit landing in a
  group's region mutates the shared group, reprojects every sibling
  instance, and stages the diff back through tm so it commits in the same
  mm:modify.
  
  gm is a constructor chunk (util.instantiate('groupManager', {tm,cm})).
  The fake tm captures the seam handlers and records staged peer ops;
  flush(trio) fires preflush, fakes mm uuid-stamping on staged adds, then
  fires postflush.

# Helpers
  @fn mk()  @ 15-19
  @fn note(ppq, chan, lane, extra)  @ 22-28
  @fn rect(ppq, chan)  @ 31-34
      -- One note:1 stream on the anchor channel, a bar wide.

# Cases
  @case 'newInstance stages a concrete copy of every group event at the new anchor'  [pure]  @ 38-52
  @case 'newInstance rejects a projection whose channel falls out of range'  [pure]  @ 56-63
  @case 'a staged edit inside one instance propagates to the sibling via the group'  [pure]  @ 67-94
  @case 'a moved group note carries its tail to the sibling (endppq shifts with ppq)'  [pure]  @ 98-125
  @case 'a create inside the region on a selected stream propagates to siblings'  [pure]  @ 129-147
  @case 'a create on a stream the region does not select is ignored'  [pure]  @ 151-161
  @case 'localMode keeps the edit local: no propagation, shared group untouched'  [pure]  @ 165-194
  @case 'editing a localMode-added event after leaving localMode does not crash'  [pure]  @ 198-221

